import pandas as pd

# Load the dataset
file_path = '2.12_Health_systems.csv'
health_systems_df = pd.read_csv(file_path)

# Display missing values
missing_values = health_systems_df.isnull().sum()
print("Missing Values by Column:")
print(missing_values)

# Option 1: Drop rows with any missing values
# health_systems_df_cleaned = health_systems_df.dropna()

# Option 2: Impute missing values
# For numerical columns
health_systems_df_imputed = health_systems_df.fillna({
    'Health_exp_pct_GDP_2016': health_systems_df['Health_exp_pct_GDP_2016'].median(),
    'Health_exp_public_pct_2016': health_systems_df['Health_exp_public_pct_2016'].median(),
    'Health_exp_out_of_pocket_pct_2016': health_systems_df['Health_exp_out_of_pocket_pct_2016'].median(),
    # Add other numerical columns here
})

# For categorical columns
health_systems_df_imputed['Country_Region'].fillna('Unknown', inplace=True)

# Option 3: Drop columns with more than 50% missing values
threshold = 0.5  # 50% missing values
health_systems_df_cleaned = health_systems_df.dropna(axis=1, thresh=int(threshold * len(health_systems_df)))

# Display cleaned data
print("\nCleaned Data Information:")
print(health_systems_df_cleaned.info())

# Select the first 20 countries/regions
top_20_countries = health_systems_df['Country_Region'].unique()[:20]

# Filter the dataset for these 20 countries/regions
filtered_df = health_systems_df[health_systems_df['Country_Region'].isin(top_20_countries)]

# Calculate the average health expenditure as a percentage of GDP for these countries/regions
avg_health_exp_pct_gdp = filtered_df.groupby('Country_Region')['Health_exp_pct_GDP_2016'].mean()

# Plot the bar chart
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 8))
avg_health_exp_pct_gdp.sort_values().plot(kind='barh', color='skyblue')
plt.xlabel('Average Health Expenditure (%)')
plt.ylabel('Country/Region')
plt.title('Health Expenditure as Percentage of GDP for Selected 20 Countries/Regions')
plt.tight_layout()
plt.savefig('top_20_health_exp_pct_gdp.png')
plt.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt


# Display the first few rows and basic information
print("First few rows of the dataset:")
print(mental_health_df.head())

print("\nBasic Information:")
print(mental_health_df.info())

# Convert columns to appropriate data types
mental_health_df['Year'] = pd.to_numeric(mental_health_df['Year'], errors='coerce')
for col in ['Schizophrenia (%)', 'Bipolar disorder (%)', 'Eating disorders (%)', 'Anxiety disorders (%)', 'Drug use disorders (%)', 'Depression (%)', 'Alcohol use disorders (%)']:
    mental_health_df[col] = pd.to_numeric(mental_health_df[col], errors='coerce')

# Drop rows with too many missing values (adjust threshold as needed)
mental_health_df_cleaned = mental_health_df.dropna(subset=['Schizophrenia (%)', 'Bipolar disorder (%)', 'Eating disorders (%)', 'Anxiety disorders (%)', 'Drug use disorders (%)', 'Depression (%)', 'Alcohol use disorders (%)'])

# Check the cleaned dataset
print("\nCleaned DataFrame:")
print(mental_health_df_cleaned.head())

import seaborn as sns

# Create a DataFrame to compare treatment and family history
treatment_family_history = mental_health_df.groupby(['family_history', 'treatment']).size().unstack().fillna(0)
treatment_family_history['Total'] = treatment_family_history.sum(axis=1)
treatment_family_history['Treatment (%)'] = (treatment_family_history['Yes'] / treatment_family_history['Total']) * 100

# Plot the bar chart
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
sns.barplot(x=treatment_family_history.index, y=treatment_family_history['Treatment (%)'], palette='pastel')
plt.xlabel('Family History of Mental Health Issues')
plt.ylabel('Percentage Receiving Treatment (%)')
plt.title('Percentage of Treatment Received by Family History of Mental Health Issues')
plt.tight_layout()
plt.savefig('treatment_vs_family_history.png')
